All alone, I'm so all alone ;
There is no one else, but you.
All alone, by the telephone ;
Wainting for a ring, a chingeling,
I'm all alone, every evening ;
All alone, feeling blue.
One ring, where you are,
And how you are,
And if you are
All alone, too.
